	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Revisiting the quest for the most accurate NES palette:</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've got a question:<br /><br />I own two TVs of exactly the same brand. I have access to the hidden system menu where I can adjust all possible values.<br />And guess what: Setting the same values in both TVs does <em>not</em> produce the same output.<br /><br />So, what makes you think that creating an &quot;accurate&quot; NES palette is a thing that would even be possible <em>in theory</em> when not even two identical TVs with exactly identical values produce even slightly the same output?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


