	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Revisiting the quest for the most accurate NES palette:</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />There is an NTSC standard for translating composite waveforms into RGB intensities, but I don't think TVs actually follow it. Instead they add quirks that in the manufacturer's opinion enhance the subjective appearance of live-action scenes that the manufacturer thinks viewers are most likely to watch, such as &quot;yellow boost&quot; in Japanese TVs.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
